# Security & Multitenant

Read `docs/security/threat-model.md` before auth/billing/PII work.

- **RLS:** every table has `tenant_id`; policies enforced in PostgreSQL.
- **JWT:** `tenant_id` from token only; middleware sets session var.
- **Input:** validate all POST/PATCH bodies; max body size; sanitize outputs.
- **Secrets:** env vars only; never log tokens, passwords, or full PAN.
- **Rate limit:** public endpoints (signup, login) — see `api-security.md`.
- **Debug:** `bypass_auth` never in staging/prod configs.

New endpoints handling money or PII → invoke security-auditor agent.
